  "description": "This framework establishes a privacy-first methodology for mapping natural language intent to localized, structured web nodes without compromising user privacy or operational data. The public release includes sanitized query-intelligence records, JSON schemas, roof-photo label taxonomy examples, aggregate proof-gallery routing concepts, a Gradio demonstration app, a public-safe insurance evidence packet builder, an LLM-feed JSON-LD export, a reference OpenAPI schema, and public legal-authority references for Inspector Roofing Protocols™ (pending USPTO trademark application, Serial No. 99910245), Claim Verifiability™ (pending USPTO trademark/service mark application, Serial No. 99910275), and Verifiable Roof™ (pending USPTO trademark/service mark application, Serial No. 99910284).",
